",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01A4mstWhKfGSHTqjf1ZxJtZ\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package agent\\n     2→\\n     3→import (\\n     4→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n     5→\\n     6→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/types\\\"\\n     7→)\\n     8→\\n     9→// AgentSession represents a coding session's data.\\n    10→// Each agent stores data in its native format (JSONL, SQLite, Markdown, etc.)\\n    11→// and only the originating agent can read/write it.\\n    12→//\\n    13→// Design: Sessions are NOT interoperable between agents. A session created by\\n    14→// Claude Code can only be read/written by Claude Code. This simplifies the\\n    15→// implementation as we don't need format conversion.\\n    16→//\\n    17→//nolint:revive // AgentSession is clearer than Session in context of the package\\n    18→type AgentSession struct {\\n    19→\\tSessionID  string\\n    20→\\tAgentName  types.AgentName\\n    21→\\tRepoPath   string\\n    22→\\tSessionRef string // Path/reference to session in agent's storage\\n    23→\\tStartTime  time.Time\\n    24→\\n    25→\\t// NativeData holds the session content in the agent's native format.\\n    26→\\t// Only the originating agent can interpret this data.\\n    27→\\t// Examples:\\n    28→\\t//   - Claude Code: raw JSONL bytes\\n    29→\\t//   - Cursor: serialized SQLite rows\\n    30→\\t//   - Aider: Markdown content\\n    31→\\tNativeData []byte\\n    32→\\n    33→\\t// Computed fields - populated by the agent when reading\\n    34→\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n    35→\\tNewFiles      []string\\n    36→\\tDeletedFiles  []string\\n    37→\\n    38→\\t// Optional normalized entries - agents may populate this if needed\\n    39→\\t// for operations that benefit from structured access\\n    40→\\tEntries []SessionEntry\\n    41→}\\n    42→\\n    43→// SessionEntry represents a single entry in the session\\n    44→type SessionEntry struct {\\n    45→\\tUUID      string\\n    46→\\tType      EntryT